            "body": "From what you've shown it sounds like the \"Highlighting\" already exists. If the tab stop has empty default text does that still get shown?\n\nEither way FWIW I think that's good enough. Though I'd consider \"Extmarks / Inlay Hints\" a nice to have for reasons listed above\n\n```python\nclass ${1:Foo}($2):\n    def __init__(self, ${3:parent}) -> None:\n        super().__init__(${3:parent})\n```\n\n> - The order of the tabstops\n> - Replacing the parent text will edit other parts of the same snippet\n> - Tab stops with no default text are clearly shown\n\nBut if that doesn't sound that useful I suppose this suggestion can be backlogged / closed. Just wanted to throw out the idea in case it interested the group",
